Fix daily report accuracy + archive system verification

## Daily Report fixes (Task #15 code review items)

### Backend: /api/reports/daily now uses all assignments (active + archived)
Previously, submitted/notSubmitted lists were computed against active-only assignments,
meaning any assignment that was later archived would drop out of historical date reports.
Now fetches both active and archived assignments in parallel and merges them before
computing eligibility and submission matching — historical reports remain accurate
regardless of archival state.

The low-attendance calculation already used active+archived; submitted/notSubmitted
now matches that same scope.

### API contract: accepts `date` (single day) or `dateFrom`+`dateTo` (range)
Frontend sends `date` for Today/Yesterday/Custom presets and `dateFrom`+`dateTo`
for This Week, matching the spec's stated `date` param for single-day queries.

### Frontend: subject always shown in report header and WhatsApp text
Previously, "All Subjects" was hidden from both the report subtitle and the WhatsApp
message body. Now always shown:
- Report subtitle: "📅 Today · 🏫 Form 1 · 📖 All Subjects"
- WhatsApp text line: "📖 Subject: All Subjects"

